de.engehausen.treemap

Interface IIteratorSize<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of element the iterator exposes
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<E>

    public interface IIteratorSize<E>
extends java.util.Iterator<E>
    An iterator that indicates the number of items it will expose.
    When dealing with a huge input tree for the layout calculation it can be beneficial to the peformance to expose this iterator, because the internal lists of the output model can be optimally sized using this iterator.
